nodes.bodyText:
@gustavonalle IMO, add a test in org.infinispan.api.CacheAPITest that tests write to the same key in the same tx:
tm.begin
assert cache.put(k, v1) == null;
assert cache.put(k, v2) == v1;
assert cache.put(k, v3) == v2
tm.commit

then you can tune the "old value" field to your use case.
AFAIK, tx never retries in the originator and remotely, it cleanups the context before replaying the transaction writes.

